public static String convertName(String name) {
    StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(name, ",");
    String firstName = st.nextToken().trim();
    String lastName = st.nextToken().trim();
    return lastName + " " + firstName;
}
```
<<<explanation>>>: This method uses the StringTokenizer class to split the input string into two parts at the comma. The first name is the token before the comma and the last name is the token after the comma. The trim() method is used to remove any leading or trailing spaces. The method then returns a string in the form "Bob Marley" by concatenating the last name, a space, and the first name.
